      <h2>Safety</h2>

      <div class="warning">
        Read all safety warnings, instructions, illustrations and specifications provided
        with this power tool. Failure to follow them may result in electric shock, fire,
        and/or serious injury. Save all warnings and instructions for future reference.
      </div>

      <h3>Specific rules for ratchets</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Hold the tool by the insulated gripping surfaces</strong> when the fastener may
          contact hidden wiring. A fastener touching a live wire energizes the exposed metal parts
          of the tool and can shock the operator.</li>
        <li>Use only <strong>impact-rated sockets and accessories</strong>. Standard sockets can
          shatter or break and cause injury.</li>
        <li>Do not use this tool on asbestos-containing products. Identify the workpiece composition
          before starting; asbestos should only be removed by a qualified professional.</li>
        <li>In dusty conditions use an OSHA-compliant dust extraction solution or wear appropriate
          respiratory protection.</li>
        <li>Maintain labels and nameplates &mdash; they carry important information. Replace any that
          are unreadable or missing.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>General use and battery care</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Always wear eye protection meeting <strong>ANSI&nbsp;Z87.1</strong>.</li>
        <li>Prevent unintentional starting &mdash; keep the lock switch engaged before picking up or
          carrying the tool.</li>
        <li>Recharge <strong>only</strong> with the specified M12&trade; charger. Charge within the
          temperature range in the charger manual.</li>
        <li>Keep an idle battery pack away from paper clips, coins, keys, nails, and other metal
          objects that can short the terminals and cause burns or fire.</li>
        <li>Do not use a damaged or modified battery pack or tool. Do not expose the pack or tool to
          fire or temperatures above 265&deg;F (130&deg;C) &mdash; it may explode.</li>
        <li>Have service performed only by qualified personnel using identical replacement parts.
          Never service a damaged battery pack yourself.</li>
      </ul>

